  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3007",
  "title": "docs(readme): Revamp README",
  "body": "This is a proposal to improve our README to become more attractive to developers relying on READMEs.\r\n\r\nAs Algolia is going more mature, I thought it would be an opportunity to work on the image of InstantSearch to appear more mature as well. We're getting more exposure so I think it's important to take time to work on this.\r\n\r\nThis PR is to trigger discussion and to work on it together. Let me know if I'm taking any wrong directions.\r\n\r\n## Main changes\r\n\r\n- Change to newer logo\r\n- Remove emojis in titles because they break hyperlinks (we can find a solution if we really need them)\r\n- Add badges to bring more confidence\r\n- Update getting started code snippet to ES2015\r\n- Link to getting started CodeSandbox\r\n- Add a clear \"Documentation\" section\r\n- Add a \"Demos\" section to see what you can build with InstantSearch.js\r\n- Add a \"Playground\" section that links to the template generated with [Create InstantSearch App](https://github.com/algolia/create-instantsearch-app)\r\n- Reword the \"Contributing\" section\r\n- Add \"License\" section\r\n\r\n## Things to consider\r\n\r\n- Need to update other flavors' README",
